Persona - Retired Woman
Cynthia, aged 67, is a retired nurse practitioner in Greyslake Illinois. 
She spends her week working around the house, or taking care of her grandchildren. 
She was born to Polish immigrants, and has three children of her own. She has a Masters degree in her field, 
and has worked remotely handling insurance claims calls for the past 15 years working through a telehealth portal.

Her experience with secure systems and multiple different logins means she understands the need for security, 
and handling the family finances for years have led her to be very cautious surrounding her families finances. 
She is interested in MapMyMint to keep track of her retirement expenses against her set budget, and would 
like to be able to look more closely at her husbands finances as he works to close his business. 
With one of her children helping with her accounting, she wants to be able to share her budget without 
having to make an excel spreadsheet every single time.


Cynthia's user stories:
As a user familiar with secure systems, I want my accounts to be secure.

As a retired person I want to be able to set a monthly budget for my map, 
because my Social Security payments don't accurately reflect my funds.

As someone who shares my budgeting, I want an easy and efficicient way to share with my children.

As a retiree managing a fixed income, I want to monitor my monthly expenses against my budget so I can ensure my savings last over time.
As someone experienced with financial responsibility, I want secure access to my financial information so I feel confident my data is protected.
As a spouse of a business owner transitioning to retirement, I want visibility into my husband’s financial activity so I can stay informed about our overall finances.
As a parent collaborating with my child on finances, I want to share my budgeting information easily so we can work together without extra manual effort.
As someone who prefers clarity, I want to review detailed breakdowns of my spending so I can make careful and informed decisions.

Requirement Specification:
When Cynthia logs into the system, the system shall require secure authentication to protect her financial information. 
The system shall display her retirement income, monthly expenses, and remaining budget in a clear summary view to help her monitor spending against her fixed income. 
While her expenses approach or exceed her set monthly budget, the system shall notify her with a visible alert. 
When Cynthia selects her husband’s linked account, the system shall display a detailed breakdown of his business-related income and expenses to support their transition into full retirement. 
When Cynthia chooses to share her budget with her child, the system shall generate a secure, shareable report without requiring her to manually create a spreadsheet. 
If unauthorized access is attempted, the system shall deny access and log the event to maintain financial security.
The system shall allow Cynthia to view her expenses compared to a predefined monthly budget so she can track her financial stability.
The system shall implement secure authentication measures to protect sensitive financial data.
The system shall provide access controls that allow Cynthia to securely view shared financial accounts, including her spouse’s financial information where permitted.
The system shall enable Cynthia to share her financial data with a trusted family member through a secure sharing feature, eliminating the need for manual spreadsheets.
The system shall present detailed expense reports with clear categorizations to support careful financial review.
The system shall allow Cynthia to filter and review transactions over customizable time periods.
If unauthorized access is attempted, the system shall notify Cynthia and take appropriate security measures to protect her account.
